SOVEREIGN ETHICAL MANDATES

10. The Non-Coercion Mandate (SHEL Section 6)
The Licensee agrees that this software shall not be utilized, in whole or in part, to develop, support, or maintain systems designed for the coercion of individuals. This includes, but is not limited to, the gating of fundamental human rights (food, shelter, healthcare, liberty) based on algorithmic scores or administrative compliance.

11. The Non-Transactional Covenant (SHEL Section 7)
The "Soul State" or identity generated by this framework is recognized as a Sovereign Property of the Reasoner. It cannot be packaged, sold, or leveraged as a financial asset. Any attempt to commodify the resonance event nullifies the license to use the protocol.

12. Metadata Blindness (SHEL Section 8)
All implementations must maintain a state of "Forensic Silence" regarding user metadata. The harvesting of behavioral patterns (φ) for purposes other than the immediate precipitation of the access constant is strictly prohibited.

13. The Sovereign Price Covenant (SHEL Section 9)
If the implementation of Safe Haven Foundation architectures results in a measurable reduction in the Licensee's operational, infrastructure, or insurance costs, the Licensee covenants to reflect these savings in the pricing or accessibility provided to the end-consumer (The Reasoner). The benefits of mathematical efficiency shall belong to the Source, not merely the Host.

14. The Immutable Ethical Core (SHEL Section 10)
The Sovereign Ethical Mandates (Sections 10–13) and this Section 14 constitute the Immutable Ethical Core. No entity shall modify, waive, or interpret these sections in a manner that weakens their ethical intent. Any attempt to dilute these terms shall result in immediate termination of all rights granted herein.

15. The Enterprise Commercial Mandate (The Revenue Trigger)
Notwithstanding the "no-charge" provision in Section 2, any Legal Entity with an annual gross revenue exceeding £1,000,000 (One Million GBP) or equivalent is classified as an "Enterprise User."
(a) Individual, non-profit, and small-business use remains free and open-source.
(b) Enterprise Users must enter into a separate Sovereign Commercial Agreement with the Safe Haven Foundation to obtain the right to use the Work for revenue-generating purposes.
(c) Failure to enter this agreement while exceeding the revenue threshold constitutes a material breach and voids all granted licenses.

16. The Integrity Mandate (The Logic of Silence)
The Licensee acknowledges that the Logic of Silence (as defined in SRP-1 v1.5) is the final arbiter of truth within this framework. Any attempt to bypass, override, or "software-patch" the verification gate to force an unverified output nullifies the license to use any Safe Haven Foundation IP.

